    • Method Detail

      • getProperty

        TokenizerProperty getProperty()
        Returns the TokenizerProperty that describes the pattern that matches data passed to PatternHandler.matches(de.susebox.jtopas.spi.DataProvider). The returned value is not null.
        Returns:
        the pattern property of a successful match

      • getLengthOfMatch

        int getLengthOfMatch()
        Returns the number of characters that are part of a match.
        Returns:
        length of match

      • getGroups

        java.lang.String[] getGroups()
                      throws TokenizerException
        Returns the capturing groups of a match. It is used if the calling tokenizer needs these groups (e. g. if the flag de.susebox.jtopas.TokenizerProperties#F_RETURN_IMAGE_PARTS is set).
        The return value must not be null or empty. The first element (array index 0) must contain the whole pattern match (as described in the Java 1.4 documentation for Matcher or the newer Java 1.5 MatchResult).
        Returns:
        the capturing groups of the last pattern match in PatternHandler.matches(de.susebox.jtopas.spi.DataProvider).
        Throws:
        TokenizerException
